# Keep the Docker build context small and deterministic. The image only needs
# site/ (the Rust crate) and the built DuckDB store from data/.

# ─── Build artifacts / VCS / tooling not needed to build the image ───
**/target
.git
.github
.claude
skills
docs
pipeline
**/__pycache__
**/*.py[cod]
**/.venv
*.md

# ─── data/: excluded entirely ────────────────────────────────────────
# The DuckDB store is bind-mounted read-only from the host at runtime (not baked
# into the image), so nothing from data/ belongs in the build context. Keeping
# the ~3.5 GB DB out of the context also makes the build far faster.
data
